Further analysis shows 'sáº¡c nhanh', 'dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t' are describing 'MÃ¡y' and 'ráº¥t nhiá»‡t tÃ¬nh' is describing 'nhÃ¢n viÃªn cá»§a tgdd', and 'nÃªn mua nhÃ© mn' is describing the shopping experience. Thus the correct format is:. MÃ¡y pin trÃ¢u, mÃ¡y sáº¡c nhanh, mÃ¡y dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t, nhÃ¢n viÃªn cá»§a tgdd ráº¥t nhiá»‡t tÃ¬nh, viá»‡c mua mÃ¡y táº¡i Ä‘Ã¢y nÃªn mua nhÃ© mn. . Final analysis shows the 'sáº¡c nhanh' should be in a separate sentence to 'MÃ¡y pin trÃ¢u' and 'dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t' to maintain subject consistency:. MÃ¡y pin trÃ¢u, mÃ¡y sáº¡c nhanh, mÃ¡y dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t, nhÃ¢n viÃªn cá»§a tgdd ráº¥t nhiá»‡t tÃ¬nh, viá»‡c mua mÃ¡y táº¡i Ä‘Ã¢y nÃªn mua nhÃ© mn. . However this does not follow the 'connected by conjunctions must be divided into individual sentences along with their conjunctions' rule:. MÃ¡y pin trÃ¢u, vÃ  mÃ¡y sáº¡c nhanh, vÃ  mÃ¡y dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t, vÃ  nhÃ¢n viÃªn cá»§a tgdd ráº¥t nhiá»‡t tÃ¬nh, vÃ  viá»‡c mua mÃ¡y táº¡i Ä‘Ã¢y nÃªn mua nhÃ© mn. . Thus the correct answer, following the 'connected by conjunctions must be divided into individual sentences along with their conjunctions' rule and specifying the subject in every sentence, and retaining the original spacings exactly as in the original sentence is:. MÃ¡y pin trÃ¢u,  mÃ¡y sáº¡c nhanh,  mÃ¡y dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t,  nhÃ¢n viÃªn cá»§a tgdd ráº¥t nhiá»‡t tÃ¬nh,  viá»‡c mua mÃ¡y táº¡i Ä‘Ã¢y nÃªn mua nhÃ© mn . . Further analysis shows 'sáº¡c nhanh', 'dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t' and 'pin trÃ¢u' should all have 'MÃ¡y' as their subject:. MÃ¡y pin trÃ¢u,  mÃ¡y sáº¡c nhanh,  mÃ¡y dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t,  vÃ  nhÃ¢n viÃªn cá»§a tgdd ráº¥t nhiá»‡t tÃ¬nh,  vÃ  ngÆ°á»i mua nÃªn mua mÃ¡y nÃ y nhÃ© mn. . So eventually becomes:. MÃ¡y cÃ³ pin trÃ¢u,  mÃ¡y sáº¡c nhanh,  mÃ¡y dÃ¹ng bao mÆ°á»£t,  vÃ  nhÃ¢n viÃªn cá»§a tgdd ráº¥t nhiá»‡t tÃ¬nh,  vÃ  ngÆ°á»i mua nÃªn mua mÃ¡y nÃ y nhÃ© mn. . Thus the final result is:.
